        <updateDate>2022-03-24T19:15:30Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill prohibits the Department of Defense (DOD) from taking specified actions against a member of the National Guard based on whether the member has received a COVID-19 vaccine. Specifically, DOD may not (1) involuntarily discharge or discipline the member, (2) withhold pay or benefits from the member, or (3) prohibit the member from participating in training or using equipment.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
